  "finger_focus": "Right pinky reaches to ' (next to ;), double quote = Shift + '",
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Two more marks earn their keep every day: the apostrophe and the double quote. The apostrophe builds contractions and shows possession; the quotes wrap anything someone actually said. A newsroom runs on both - get a quote wrong and you have misquoted a person, not just a sentence."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "The apostrophe sits just right of the semicolon, on the home row - your right pinky barely moves to reach it. The double quote is the same key with Shift: hold Shift with your left pinky, tap the quote key with your right. Same finger does both jobs; the only difference is the Shift."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "✍️",
      "title": "Quotes come in pairs",
      "text": "Every opening quote needs a closing one. Type both as you go - \"hello\" - so you never leave a quote hanging. And contractions hold no space: it's, don't, that's are single words, fused at the apostrophe."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "'",
      "baseReps": 15,
      "keys": ["'"],
      "target": "' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' '",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "The apostrophe",
      "hint": "Right pinky taps the key right of the semicolon, then home. No Shift."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "\"",
      "baseReps": 15,
      "keys": ["\""],
      "target": "\" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \"",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "The double quote",
      "hint": "Left pinky holds Shift, right pinky taps the same key. Hold, tap, release."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Now the practical work: contractions that close up tight, and a line of quoted speech with its pair of marks. Read each phrase, then type it - no space inside a contraction, a matched pair around every quote."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "A quote is a promise: those are the words, in that order. Type them as carefully as you would print them.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "it's a fact. don't worry. she said \"hello\" and smiled. that's the way it's done.",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Contractions and speech",
      "hint": "No space inside it's or don't; open and close every quote."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Steps done? Open the trainer below and take one clean run at the full lesson text. That run saves your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
    }
  ],
